{"reasoning":"I consolidated the two small cache helper functions into a single, unambiguous function that always writes the current user name into the cache. Previously there were two helpers: sync_user_to_cache (which unconditionally overwrote the cache) and refresh_user_snapshot (which used cache_put_if_absent and could leave stale values). That difference caused a bug where saving a user with a new name sometimes did not update the cache.

Changes made:
- Removed refresh_user_snapshot and kept a single sync_user_to_cache that always calls cache_put (overwrites existing value).
- Updated all callers (user_service.bulk_warm_cache and imports) to use the unified sync_user_to_cache.
- Left other cache helper functions intact.

This preserves intended behavior for saving/renaming users (cache now updates to the latest name) and makes bulk_warm_cache consistent with save_user/rename_user.
